# Copy to server/.env and fill values. Never commit real secrets.
# Optional: server/.env.local overrides these (gitignored).
#
# --- Local development (minimal checklist) ---
# 1) PostgreSQL running; DATABASE_URL=postgresql://…
# 2) JWT_ACCESS_SECRET and JWT_REFRESH_SECRET (each >= 32 chars, different values)
# 3) STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_… to exercise Checkout (see Stripe Dashboard)
# 4) PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=false for local Checkout / wallet / recharge routes (default in snippet below)
# 5) Flutter web: default API is http://127.0.0.1:8787 — see repo README + lib/core/config/app_config.dart
# 6) Quieter logs while testing auth only: RELOADLY_AF_PROBE_ON_STARTUP=false (Reloadly code stays enabled)
#
# === Required for API startup (see src/index.js) ===
# DATABASE_URL — PostgreSQL connection string (postgresql://…)
# JWT_ACCESS_SECRET — >= 32 characters, unique random string
# JWT_REFRESH_SECRET — >= 32 characters, different from JWT_ACCESS_SECRET
#
# === Stripe (test mode: sk_test_… / live: sk_live_…) ===
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY — API secret from Dashboard (server-only)
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET — whsec_… from Dashboard webhook endpoint or `stripe listen` output.
#   Required when PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=true. Strongly recommended for any checkout webhook testing.
#
# === Lockdown & CORS ===
# PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN — true = money routes return 503; strict CORS; extra startup checks.
#   false = allow POST /create-checkout-session, /api/wallet/topup, /api/recharge/order (still auth + rate limits).
# CORS_ORIGINS — comma-separated full origins. Production: no * (startup fails on wildcards).
#   When PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=true in production, use explicit CORS_ORIGINS only.
#   In development, localhost / 127.0.0.1 on any port are allowed for Flutter web (see corsPolicy.js).
#
# === Production-only (index.js enforces when NODE_ENV=production) ===
# CLIENT_URL — HTTPS app origin for Stripe success/cancel (no trailing slash)
# ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL / REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL — set explicitly in production
#
# === Optional ===
# WEBTOPUP_FULFILLMENT_PROVIDER — `mock` (default) | `reloadly` for WebTopupOrder admin dispatch (AF + airtime only initially).
#   When `reloadly`, RELOADLY_CLIENT_ID and RELOADLY_CLIENT_SECRET must be set (startup validates).
# WEBTOPUP_FULFILLMENT_ASYNC — `true` to enqueue WebTopupFulfillmentJob after QUEUED (provider I/O off HTTP path; worker polls).
# WEBTOPUP_FULFILLMENT_JOB_POLL_MS — worker interval in ms (default 3000; set 0 to disable in-process polling).
# LOYALTY_POINTS_USD_BASIS_CENTS — cents per 1 loyalty point (default 100 → $1 = 1 point). No randomness; grants on delivered orders only.
# WEBTOPUP_FAILSIM — mock only: timeout | retry | terminal | unsupported (failure simulation).
# NODE_ENV — defaults to development if unset (see src/config/env.js)
# LOG_LEVEL — info | debug | …
# PORT — default 8787
#
# Prisma CLI: use npm run db:migrate / db:validate so server/bootstrap.js loads server/.env
# before Prisma runs (avoids stale DATABASE_URL in the shell on Windows).

# Server
PORT=8787
NODE_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Database — PostgreSQL only (Prisma)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/zora_walat?schema=public
# Optional: separate DB for server integration tests (`npm run test:ci`). CI sets this automatically.
# When set (non-empty), integration preload copies this to DATABASE_URL for the test process — that DB MUST be migrated.
# Migrate the same URL the tests use: from server/, `npm run db:migrate:integration` (avoid relying on `db:migrate` alone if you only updated .env DATABASE_URL but tests still use TEST_DATABASE_URL).
# Quiet the integration DB banner in test stderr: ZW_INTEGRATION_DB_LOG=0
# Example local DB name (create empty DB, then `npm run db:migrate:integration`):
# TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/zora_test?schema=public
# TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/zora_walat_phase1_test?schema=public

# Reverse-proxy hops for Express (production only). Default 1. Use 2 if CDN + LB.
# TRUST_PROXY_HOPS=1

# Stripe — Secret key from Dashboard (server-only; not pk_…)
# Optional: one-line file server/stripe_secret.key instead (gitignored)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=

# Stripe webhook signing secret (Dashboard → Webhooks → signing secret). Server-only.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# TEMP — local-only API auth bypass without JWT (non-production; startup fails if enabled with NODE_ENV=production).
# Applies to any route using `requireAuth` (wallet, /auth/me, etc.): send header `X-ZW-Dev-Checkout: <secret>`.
# DEV_CHECKOUT_AUTH_BYPASS=true
# DEV_CHECKOUT_BYPASS_SECRET= — >=16 chars; must match Flutter --dart-define=DEV_CHECKOUT_BYPASS_SECRET
# DEV_CHECKOUT_BYPASS_USER_ID= — existing User.id in DB (wallet top-up credits this user)

# Stripe Checkout return URLs (production only):
# Set your deployed web app origin, no trailing slash (e.g. https://app.example.com).
# In development, leave unset — the API uses the browser `Origin` header from the checkout POST.
# CLIENT_URL=

# CORS: comma-separated full origins. No * or wildcards (production startup fails if invalid).
# PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=true: only http://localhost:3000 and http://127.0.0.1:3000 are allowed (exact match).
# If unset under pre-launch, those two are applied by default.
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=true — zero–money-movement mode:
# - Blocks POST /create-checkout-session, POST /api/wallet/topup, POST /api/recharge/order (503).
# - Strict CORS to localhost:3000 / 127.0.0.1:3000 only.
# - Requires DATABASE_URL, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, JWT secrets; minimal HTTP access logs only.
# PRELAUNCH_LOCKDOWN=false

# JWT auth — server-only. Generate strong random strings (≥32 chars each), different values.
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=replace_with_at_least_32_character_random_secret_a
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=replace_with_at_least_32_character_random_secret_b
# Access token TTL (seconds). Production: must set explicitly.
ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL=900
# Refresh token TTL (seconds). Production: must set explicitly.
REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL=604800

# Pricing engine (USD checkout). Tune Stripe fee to match your Stripe pricing.
# PRICING_STRIPE_FEE_BPS=290
# PRICING_STRIPE_FIXED_CENTS=30
# PRICING_FX_BPS=0
# PRICING_TAX_BPS=0
# Amount-only airtime: wholesale as basis points of selected face value (9000 = 90%).
# PRICING_AMOUNT_ONLY_PROVIDER_BPS=9000

# Phase 1 — profit floor & minimum order (USD checkout; mobile top-up only).
# Net margin = (final − Stripe fee − provider − fx/tax buffer − risk buffer) / final.
# PHASE1_MIN_MARGIN_PERCENT=3
# PHASE1_TARGET_MARGIN_PERCENT=4.5
# PHASE1_MAX_MARGIN_PERCENT=6
# PHASE1_MIN_CHECKOUT_USD_CENTS=1000
# PHASE1_RECOMMENDED_MIN_CHECKOUT_USD_CENTS=1500
# Emergency only — allow checkouts below min (default false; never enable in production without review).
# PHASE1_ALLOW_BELOW_MINIMUM_ORDERS=false

# Financial truth — Stripe fee estimate vs actual (anomaly: STRIPE_FEE_DIVERGENCE).
# FINANCIAL_TRUTH_STRIPE_FEE_TOLERANCE_CENTS=50
# FINANCIAL_TRUTH_STRIPE_FEE_TOLERANCE_RATIO_BPS=1500

# Margin intelligence (admin analytics): flag low net-to-sell routes (500 = 5%).
# MARGIN_LOW_ROUTE_BP=500

# Referral program — optional overrides (else use ReferralProgramConfig in DB).
# REFERRAL_ENABLED=true
# REFERRAL_REWARD_USD=5
# REFERRAL_WEEKLY_BUDGET_USD=50
# REFERRAL_MIN_FIRST_ORDER_USD=2
# REFERRAL_MAX_REWARDS_PER_INVITER_WEEK=10
# REFERRAL_EVAL_DELAY_MS=300000
# REFERRAL_PRIVACY_SALT= — optional HMAC salt for IP/device correlation (defaults to JWT_ACCESS_SECRET)
#
# REFERRAL_EVALUATION_SCHEDULING_ENABLED — default on. Set false to block background scheduling of
#   referral evaluation after deliveries (no automatic credit path from delayed jobs).
#
# LOYALTY_AUTO_GRANT_ON_DELIVERY — default on. Set false to suppress automatic loyalty point grants
#   when an order reaches a delivered/fulfilled state (audit still records suppression).

# Production safety (NODE_ENV=production): startup fails if mock airtime or mock web-top-up fulfillment
# is used without explicit opt-in (see server/docs/PHASE1_PRODUCTION_SAFETY_GATES.md).
# ALLOW_MOCK_AIRTIME_IN_PRODUCTION=true
# ALLOW_MOCK_WEBTOPUP_FULFILLMENT_IN_PRODUCTION=true
#
# Airtime fulfillment — server-only API; never embed in Flutter/web or public env.
# AIRTIME_PROVIDER=mock
# AIRTIME_PROVIDER_TIMEOUT_MS=30000
# RELOADLY_CLIENT_ID=
# RELOADLY_CLIENT_SECRET=
# RELOADLY_SANDBOX=true
# RELOADLY_ALLOW_UNAVAILABLE_MOCK_FALLBACK — default false. When true and AIRTIME_PROVIDER=reloadly, allow mock airtime
#   if Reloadly OAuth/credentials are unavailable (never implicit from NODE_ENV).
# RELOADLY_ALLOW_UNAVAILABLE_MOCK_FALLBACK=false
# RELOADLY_INQUIRY_BEFORE_RETRY_DISABLED — default false. When true, skips GET /reports/transactions before a retrying POST (emergency/tests only).
# RELOADLY_TRANSACTION_INQUIRY_MAX_PAGES — max pages (50 rows each) for unfiltered report scan (default 5).
# RELOADLY_CIRCUIT_BREAKER_DISABLED — default false. When true, disables sliding-window pause on Reloadly POST error bursts.
# FULFILLMENT_PROVIDER_CIRCUIT_WINDOW_MS — sample window in ms (default 60000).
# FULFILLMENT_PROVIDER_CIRCUIT_MIN_SAMPLES — min samples before opening circuit (default 12).
# FULFILLMENT_PROVIDER_CIRCUIT_FAILURE_RATIO — open when failure ratio exceeds this (default 0.15).
# RELOADLY_CIRCUIT_REDIS_LIST_MAX — max Redis LIST entries retained for distributed circuit samples (default 300).
# RELOADLY_CIRCUIT_RATE_LIMIT_SOFT_MIN — count of 429-class samples in window to enter soft backoff (default 4).
# RELOADLY_IDEMPOTENCY_REGISTRY_TTL_SECONDS — TTL for Redis idempotency result registry (default 604800).
# RELOADLY_TOPUP_IN_FLIGHT_TTL_SECONDS — POST in-flight marker TTL for stalled-verification detection (default 600).
# RELOADLY_STALLED_VERIFICATION_RECENT_MS — DB startedAt recency for stalled hold (default 300000).
# RELOADLY_BASE_URL — optional; defaults to sandbox or production topups host from RELOADLY_SANDBOX
# RELOADLY_BASE_URL=https://topups-sandbox.reloadly.com
# RELOADLY_AUTH_URL — optional OAuth token endpoint (default https://auth.reloadly.com/oauth/token)
# RELOADLY_AUTH_URL=https://auth.reloadly.com/oauth/token
# RELOADLY_OPERATOR_MAP_JSON — internal operatorKey → Reloadly numeric operator id (JSON object, server-only).
# Merges with defaults in server/src/config/reloadlyOperatorIdDefaults.js (non-empty env keys win).
# Example: {"roshan":"12345","mtn":"67890","etisalat":"111","afghanwireless":"222"}
# RELOADLY_OPERATOR_MAP_JSON=
# FULFILLMENT_DRAIN_INTERVAL_MS — background drain for queued attempts (ms). Default 120000; 0 disables. See src/index.js.
# FULFILLMENT_DRAIN_INTERVAL_MS=120000
#
# Stuck PROCESSING recovery (PaymentCheckout — app recharge path). Does not change Stripe or checkout payloads.
# PROCESSING_TIMEOUT_MS=600000 — treat as stuck if orderStatus=PROCESSING and updatedAt older than this.
# PROCESSING_RECOVERY_POLL_MS=60000 — in-process tick interval; 0 disables worker.
# PROCESSING_RECOVERY_MAX_ATTEMPTS=3 — auto recoveries per order (stored in metadata.processingRecovery.count) before FAILED.
# PROCESSING_RECOVERY_ENABLED=false — disable detection/recovery worker (default true when unset).
# PROCESSING_RECOVERY_SANDBOX_CONSERVATIVE=true — with RELOADLY_SANDBOX + AIRTIME_PROVIDER=reloadly, block
#   automatic retry_new_attempt (stuck processing → manual review instead of new attempt / new customIdentifier).
#
# Manual-required alerts (structured console JSON; safe suffixes only):
# MANUAL_REQUIRED_ALERT_COUNT_THRESHOLD=5 — warn when open manual-required PROCESSING rows ≥ this
# MANUAL_REQUIRED_AGED_MS=3600000 — emit manual_required_aged per stale flag (first detection time)
# MANUAL_REQUIRED_ACTION_REASON_MIN_LEN=8 — admin safe-retry/fail/mark-reviewed reason length
# RELOADLY_AF_PROBE_ON_STARTUP=false — skip Afghanistan operator probe on boot (quieter logs when testing auth only).

# === Redis (optional) ===
# REDIS_URL — Redis connection string for distributed anti-abuse state (server-only).
# Example: redis://127.0.0.1:6379/0
# REDIS_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MS — Redis connect timeout (ms). Default 2000.
# REDIS_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MS=2000

# === Phase 1 PaymentCheckout fulfillment queue (BullMQ; requires REDIS_URL) ===
# FULFILLMENT_QUEUE_ENABLED=true — webhook/client schedule enqueues jobs; run `npm run worker:fulfillment` separately.
# PHASE1_FULFILLMENT_WORKER_CONCURRENCY=5 — BullMQ Phase 1 worker parallelism (default 5; must be ≥ 1).
# FULFILLMENT_WORKER_CONCURRENCY=32 — legacy general env; Phase 1 BullMQ worker uses PHASE1_FULFILLMENT_WORKER_CONCURRENCY.
# FULFILLMENT_JOB_MAX_ATTEMPTS=8 — BullMQ attempts for thrown transient errors (default 8).
# FULFILLMENT_JOB_BACKOFF_MS=2000 — exponential backoff base (default 2000).
# FULFILLMENT_CLIENT_EXECUTE_WAIT_MS=120000 — postExecute polls DB until terminal or HTTP 504 (default 120000).
# Fortress / concurrency probe (scripts/transaction-fortress-concurrency-probe.mjs):
# FORTRESS_PROBE_AIRTIME_PROVIDER=mock — required for provider-independent queue proof (default when unset).
# FORTRESS_PROBE_ALLOW_NON_MOCK=true — allow Reloadly-backed fortress (outcomes depend on sandbox/API).
# FORTRESS_PROBE_USE_FULFILLMENT_QUEUE=true — requires REDIS_URL + FULFILLMENT_QUEUE_ENABLED=true.
#
# METRICS_PROMETHEUS_ENABLED=true — enables GET /metrics (Prometheus text/plain). With queue + multi-replica, set METRICS_REDIS_AGGREGATION=true.
# METRICS_REDIS_AGGREGATION=true — increment counters + HTTP latency histograms in Redis (`zora:metrics:v2:counters`); /metrics merges cluster totals.
#
# Scale / wallet hardening (see scripts/gate-check.mjs --scale):
# REQUIRE_WALLET_TOPUP_IDEMPOTENCY_KEY=true — reject wallet top-up without Idempotency-Key (Flutter sends UUID).
#   Only the literal string `true` enables enforcement (unset = off; matches env.js).
# WALLET_TOPUP_MAX_USD_CENTS — single-request credit cap in USD cents (default 1000000 = $10,000). Production: set lower (e.g. 50000 = $500).
# DEBUG_WALLET_TOPUP=true — stdout traces in userWalletService (TOPUP START / LEDGER INSERTED / BALANCE UPDATED / LEDGER COUNT).
# WALLET_TOPUP_PER_MINUTE_MAX — override rolling 1m top-up cap per user+IP (default prod 12, dev 40).
# WALLET_STRICT_LEDGER_VERIFY=true — HTTP 500 if post-topup `balanceUsdCents` ≠ main-balance ledger reasons only (see docs/WALLET_LEDGER_INVARIANT.md).
# FULFILLMENT_JOB_MAX_ATTEMPTS / FULFILLMENT_JOB_BACKOFF_MS — BullMQ Phase 1 fulfillment retries (exponential backoff).
# PHASE1_RECON_PRE_HTTP_ARMED_STALE_MS=600000 — recon window for stale Reloadly pre-HTTP arm (default 10m).
# SCALE_GATE_REQUIRE_REDIS_METRICS_AGGREGATION=false — opt out of cluster-metrics requirement in scale gate.
# SCALE_GATE_ALLOW_MOCK_AIRTIME=true — allow AIRTIME_PROVIDER=mock in `--scale` checks (staging only).
# INSTANCE_ID — optional logical replica id for metrics metadata (defaults HOSTNAME).

# === Web top-up fulfillment hardening (AF + airtime scope unchanged) ===
# FULFILLMENT_DISPATCH_ENABLED — default on; set false to reject all web top-up dispatch/retry (503).
# FULFILLMENT_DISPATCH_KILL_SWITCH — emergency stop; all dispatch/retry return 503 immediately.
# RELOADLY_WEBTOPUP_PROVIDER_ACTIVE — default on; set false to block Reloadly adapter while mock may still work.
# WEBTOPUP_VELOCITY_SESSION_WINDOW_MS — rolling window for session create burst signals (default 600000).
# WEBTOPUP_VELOCITY_SESSION_ORDERS_WARN — soft fraud flag threshold (default 8).
# WEBTOPUP_VELOCITY_PHONE_HOUR_ORDERS_WARN — per phone+country per UTC hour (default 12).
# WEBTOPUP_VELOCITY_PHONE_HOUR_SAME_AMOUNT_WARN — same amount repetition in hour (default 6).
# User.role for staff: admin | operator | viewer — operators can dispatch with JSON { "reason": "…" } (min 8 chars).

# === Push notifications (FCM) — inbox + device tokens; does not touch payment/fulfillment code paths ===
# PUSH_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED — default on; set false to record inbox rows but skip FCM sends.
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON — single-line JSON of Firebase service account (same as GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS file).
# PUSH_LOYALTY_PER_HOUR_MAX — cap loyalty category notifications per user per rolling hour (default 4).

# Optional overrides (server/.env.local loads after .env and overrides)
